items.title: Man arrested after minivan chase in Melbourne
items.standfirst: T he van driver allegedly collided head on with another car after police called off a pursuit.
items.content: A man is under police guard in hospital after a minivan chase in Melbourne early this morning.Police spotted the van, which they allege was of interest in an ongoing investigation, travelling on Leakes Road, Truganina, at about 4am. Officers covertly followed the van along the West Gate Freeway until it exited at the Kings Way off-ramp and started travelling toward the city.READ MORE: Charges three months after 'amazing' man killed in alleged hit-run Police deployed stop sticks on Kings Way, which slowed the van, but the driver allegedly refused to pull over. A pursuit began but was called off when the van crossed onto the wrong side of the road.A short time later, the van collided head-on with a car on the Kings Way Bridge.The van driver suffered non-life-threatening injuries and was taken to hospital under police guard. READ MORE: 'Deeply troubling': Author's dogged pursuit of the truth 50 years after Whitlam dismissal Two males in the car suffered injuries and were treated at the scene.Police allegedly found a large amount of drugs in the van.Kings Way remains shut in both directions this morning and an investigation is underway. Any witnesses or anybody with footage is urged to contact Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000 or online. Available on the Apple App Store and Google Play.
